My firm and I order from here multiple times a week. We normally love the food. This time I tried their fried oyster platter. The oysters were complete mush. I brought it back only to be told that is how oysters are. (I have had oysters before) I asked if she would eat it and she responded again with that is how the oysters are. I was told as per the owners they don't do returns or refunds because of low business due to COVID. I asked if the owners would prefer the loss of an entire customer vs the loss of the price of a meal during Covid and was told "yes" with a smile.  I love the food and love to support local businesses but my firm wont be ordering from here again.  Poor customer service.

I spent $60 at this establishment. I made a first order and waited 30 minutes for it. In the midst of waiting, I decided to order shrimp. After an hour, I had to hunt down the manager and staff to retrieve my food. Once I received my food, my fried food was cold and old. The shrimp I ordered was crunchy and undone. Now, I am at risk of food poisoning. I asked the manager for my money back because you cannot serve customers cold seafood nor undone seafood. She graciously offered 10% of our total (unacceptable) or if we wanted to wait for the plates to be cooked again. We already wasted 1 hour and 30 minutes plus $60. We weren’t going to stay for another hour for a plate of undone or uncooked food. I will never dine here again because I felt like the management didn’t value my patronage nor my money.

I really wanted to like and support this business since its closer than Red Crab House in Laurel and Hook and Reel in Largo but unfortunately, that was not the case. They do not offer 1/2 lbs of seafood options or create your own seafood bags like the other places I mentioned. They are in a high rent area so I get why the prices are higher but if you want to charge higher prices,  serve quality food and give people EVERYTHING listed that's suppose to come with the meal. I ordered the shrimp to go (which upon getting home had the head on, which isn't stated on the menu), ordered the mix seasoning and medium heat. It was bland and I had to add hot sauce and Old Bay. I was missing the sausage AND not given the option of rice/noodles/bread/etc (which I didn't get either). It was not busy so I dunno how that was missed. I also ordered the $12.95 gumbo and despite the price, liked that I could substitute the white rice with the jambalaya for only $1. The gumbo was ok but Hook and Reel makes an AMAZING seafood-filled gumbo for half the price. The jambalaya was good and very well seasoned but shrimp was thrown on top and didn't looked cooked. I put the shrimp in hot water hoping they would cook but they continued to be gray (which I have never seen before). The one bright spot is the customer service; the employees were extremely nice and attentive. I appreciate great customer service and they were excellent. Unfortunately I won't be back.
I love seafood & they have plenty of it. Cranberry mimosas are good too

I called around 1:45 to order some crab fries for pickup but I was informed that you can only place orders on grubhub or come into the restaurant.  Once i got there shortly after calling, i saw that the place was closed. Luckily I called and was informed that the kitchen closed at 2 but said that they'd make the fries for me. I dont know why the employee didnt tell me they'd be closing shortly when i called but I'm glad the woman worked with me. I got the garlic crab fries for $17. It took them less than 5 minutes for them to prepare it so the food was obviously sitting around. I expected a bit more crab for that price. It wasnt nearly as much crab as i seen on these posted pictures. The crab didnt taste like much. The large amount of garlic in the fries overpowered any taste that might've been there.I've never seen so much garlic in food, normally garlic is cut up fine but i had big chunks of garlic, so much garlic that i could've used it for another meal. If anything, i can say they definitely use fresh garlic. I've added a picture of all the garlic that i didnt eat. This will be my first and last visit here.

I purchased the seafood boil from this establishment a week ago and really enjoyed this item. The portions and quality of snow crab, shrimp, mussels and crawfish was well worth the money. I purchased again from this establishment last night and ordered the seafood jambalaya with a caesar salad. Words cannot describe how dreadful the seafood jambalaya tasted and was prepared. It was a bland mess with barely any shrimp, chicken or sausage period. They basically dumped a ton of raw tomato sauce atop overcooked mushy rice and barely included any meat items into this unholy concoction. It was completely opposite of what was demonstrated with my previous experience with the seafood boil. I actually had to doublecheck and see if I ordered from the same establishment, as this menu item was not even edible especially for the $15 price tag. It was depressing to know I wasted my money on a bowl of bland slop with barely any shrimp, chicken or sausage. This item is a disrespectful representation of Cajun food period, especially if you've had quality Cajun cuisine prior to encountering this tragedy. This establishment is clearly capable of producing quality cuisine as it was demonstrated in my previous purchase, but I'm at a loss this time around as I wasted $15 on the seafood jambalaya which I could not consume. The only reason I put 1 star in my review was due to the caesar salad that I also ordered being decent and tasty. This was not enough to overshadow the horrific result of the seafood jambalaya. This establishment needs to either overhaul or delete this item from their  food menu permanently. Hopefully any potential patrons of this establishment take heed to my warning and refrain from facing disappointment by purchasing the seafood jambalaya.

This restaurant has a unique perspective on seafood boils. The Cajun Asian fusion is most found in their sauce. The vibe is so chill and great! The staff are friendly, expedient, and attractive (especially the guys at the bar and on the floor). I love the crab legs with the extra spicy mixed sauce. Definitely go for the fried baskets and the crab fries. The gumbo, jambalaya, and etoufee are not my favorite. The owners are very polite and will definitely have a conversation with you. Overall, I recommend that anyone who likes seafood and like trying new perspectives on original cuisine, should come to this place. Please don't try to compare it to HooknReel or Hot Juicy because they all do this differently. And if you grab a drink, go for the Rum Punch or mimosas during brunch!

They had just said last call before we came but the bartender and kitchen accommodated us. The bartender allowed us to order 2 drinks and our food was hot and perfect! Everytime i come to BeClaws it is an experience. Ive been 4 times so far. Most of the time i get the seafood pot with the mild lemon sauce. Ive never had an issue, service was always wonderful. The presentation is awesome. I had been looking for a reliable place i could go to for when I wanted something great and im glad i found it. If you get a seafood pot with sauce dont hesitate to order some rice along with it. The sausage and potato inside the pot with everything is divine. The crab legs arent small, the crawfish are good and so is the shrimp. The clam chowder is AMAZING! The crab dip i would give a 3/5 it should be chunkier and have a bit more meat in it. The shrimp tacos were marvelous. A little messy but everyone has a way of doing things. The fried shrimp basket was ok, a bit overcooked but the fries (garlic) (yes you can choose what kind of fries you get )rescued the dish. The atmosphere is peaceful and its a good place to for a girls night or a family dinner. The price range is anywhere from 15-100 and up depending on how many people and your add ons. The staff is very accommodating and I cant wait to go back!  TIP: when getting the lemon seafood pot tell them to go light on the garlic

I ordered a pound of crawfish and gumbo and both were mediocre at best. I got the crawfish extra spicy and they were spicy in all the wrong ways. They taste like the crawfish was boiled with out any seasoning in the boil then a ton was thrown in the bag and tossed around which smells and looks good but leaves the inside completely bland. I grew up on the gulf eating crawfish and I’m a big crawfish person. I mean I grew up sucking the head of the crawfish for the juice these ones just taste of dirt. They really need to get the seasoning all the way through. The gumbo was just bland it taste of store bought premade gumbo. The roux was extra thick like gravy which doesn’t make for a good gumbo cause none of the juice can be absorbed in the pieces inside the gumbo. The shrimp also came on the side and wasn’t seasoned so when you put it in the gumbo now you have another bland element in it. It had a sweet taste but not the smooth spice that usually comes with gumbo. I am simply disappointed. For the price and what you actually get it doesn’t match up. They need to learn to season all there food properly and not after the fact. This place is trying to be a nice restaurant and crawfish isn’t that type of food and their trying to make it so. It just all comes off bad. But the inside of the restaurant is very beautiful.

Disappointing.
